# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Other | Scene: HuntingTheBeast3
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "They awoke early the next day to continue their exploration of the forest."
    new "They awoke early the next day to continue their exploration of the forest."

    old "The area up ahead had been where Garret said most of the Beast's tracks were usually discovered."
    new "The area up ahead had been where Garret said most of the Beast's tracks were usually discovered."

    old "If the creature had been here recently, they would surely find evidence of it."
    new "If the creature had been here recently, they would surely find evidence of it."

    old "Neither had spoken much of what had transpired the night before."
    new "Neither had spoken much of what had transpired the night before."

    old "Sarah didn't know how to bring it up, nor did it seem, did Garret."
    new "Sarah didn't know how to bring it up, nor did it seem, did Garret."

    old "Walking further through the thick forest, it seemed to Sarah that they were entirely lost."
    new "Walking further through the thick forest, it seemed to Sarah that they were entirely lost."

    old "Despite this, Garret kept assuring her that he knew where they were going."
    new "Despite this, Garret kept assuring her that he knew where they were going."

    old "He certainly seemed to move with a purpose."
    new "He certainly seemed to move with a purpose."

    old "Hang on."
    new "Hang on."

    old "You're going too fast."
    new "You're going too fast."

    old "Sarah watched as Garret kept his pace."
    new "Sarah watched as Garret kept his pace."

    old "Unlike her, he didn't have a cumbersome armor holding him down."
    new "Unlike her, he didn't have a cumbersome armor holding him down."

    old "We're almost there."
    new "We're almost there."

    old "Garret! Slow down!"
    new "Garret! Slow down!"

    old "Keep up. Just a little way more."
    new "Keep up. Just a little way more."

    old "Sarah struggled as best she could, increasing her own pace."
    new "Sarah struggled as best she could, increasing her own pace."

    old "With every step, she could feel a vine, snagging on her heel. Catching her shoulder."
    new "With every step, she could feel a vine, snagging on her heel. Catching her shoulder."

    old "Garret!"
    new "Garret!"

    old "He was so far, she nearly lost sight of him."
    new "He was so far, she nearly lost sight of him."

    old "Sarah could feel her hear begin to race."
    new "Sarah could feel her hear begin to race."

    old "Then, suddenly, the forest opened up again."
    new "Then, suddenly, the forest opened up again."

    old "Sarah stumbled through the brush, nearly falling to her knees."
    new "Sarah stumbled through the brush, nearly falling to her knees."

    old "She only barely kept her balance."
    new "She only barely kept her balance."

    old "I told you to slow down!"
    new "I told you to slow down!"

    old "She saw Garret standing in front of a great tree. Larger than any she had ever seen in her life."
    new "She saw Garret standing in front of a great tree. Larger than any she had ever seen in her life."

    old "He seemed entranced."
    new "He seemed entranced."

    old "What is this place?"
    new "What is this place?"

    old "No answer came."
    new "No answer came."

    old "Garret! Tell me what this place is! Now!"
    new "Garret! Tell me what this place is! Now!"

    old "Sarah could feel herself losing her temper with him."
    new "Sarah could feel herself losing her temper with him."

    old "Just as she was about to reach out to him, he turned and faced her."
    new "Just as she was about to reach out to him, he turned and faced her."

    old "I want to ask you for your forgiveness."
    new "I want to ask you for your forgiveness."

    old "Sarah felt a terror rising up from deep in her chest."
    new "Sarah felt a terror rising up from deep in her chest."

    old "What are you talking about."
    new "What are you talking about."

    old "I...I lied to you."
    new "I...I lied to you."

    old "Lied?"
    new "Lied?"

    old "She saw his face, shaking."
    new "She saw his face, shaking."

    old "Garret nervously stumbled to the corners of the clearing. At each point, he kneeled and placed down one of the wooden totems."
    new "Garret nervously stumbled to the corners of the clearing. At each point, he kneeled and placed down one of the wooden totems."

    old "These totems will distract the Woodland spirits. For a while at least."
    new "These totems will distract the Woodland spirits. For a while at least."

    old "Sarah studied him. His body movement was anxious. Fidgety. It seemed odd on so large a man."
    new "Sarah studied him. His body movement was anxious. Fidgety. It seemed odd on so large a man."

    old "I want to be truthful with you, because I have to ask you to do something for me."
    new "I want to be truthful with you, because I have to ask you to do something for me."

    old "What do you need me to do?"
    new "What do you need me to do?"

    old "Sarah was in little mood to humor him."
    new "Sarah was in little mood to humor him."

    old "He looked directly at her."
    new "He looked directly at her."

    old "I need you to kill me."
    new "I need you to kill me."

    old "Garret stumbled down to his knees, gripping at her hands."
    new "Garret stumbled down to his knees, gripping at her hands."

    old "The words lingered for a while. For a moment, Sarah even thought she had misheard him."
    new "The words lingered for a while. For a moment, Sarah even thought she had misheard him."

    old "I...kill you? Have you lost your mind? Why would I do something like that?"
    new "I...kill you? Have you lost your mind? Why would I do something like that?"

    old "He let his head drop into his hands, sighing deeply."
    new "He let his head drop into his hands, sighing deeply."

    old "Gods...where do I even begin."
    new "Gods...where do I even begin."

    old "The Beast...is me."
    new "The Beast...is me."

    old "I wounded all those people. I hurt them. I...killed them."
    new "I wounded all those people. I hurt them. I...killed them."

    old "You...you're a murderer?"
    new "You...you're a murderer?"

    old "She could see Garret's eyes sparkle from the tears. Some streamed down his face."
    new "She could see Garret's eyes sparkle from the tears. Some streamed down his face."

    old "I never wanted to do it...all those innocent people...Gods what a disaster."
    new "I never wanted to do it...all those innocent people...Gods what a disaster."

    old "Garret, tell me what is going on. Speak clearly."
    new "Garret, tell me what is going on. Speak clearly."

    old "She saw Garret wipe the tears from his face, clearing his throat."
    new "She saw Garret wipe the tears from his face, clearing his throat."

    old "It started almost half a year ago..."
    new "It started almost half a year ago..."

    old "My sister...she had been dead by then for more than a year."
    new "My sister...she had been dead by then for more than a year."

    old "Her favorite festival was always the harvest festival in town, and that year, I sat in my house."
    new "Her favorite festival was always the harvest festival in town, and that year, I sat in my house."

    old "I could hear the people...celebrating. And I was alone. Every cheer, a reminder that I would never hear my sister's voice again."
    new "I could hear the people...celebrating. And I was alone. Every cheer, a reminder that I would never hear my sister's voice again."

    old "Without her...without my father...I was alone."
    new "Without her...without my father...I was alone."

    old "She watched as Garret's shoulders fell."
    new "She watched as Garret's shoulders fell."

    old "So that night I decided, if there was nothing to live for...why bother to go on living?"
    new "So that night I decided, if there was nothing to live for...why bother to go on living?"

    old "I came out here, deep in the forest, to this place. One of her favorite spots. Not far from where she died."
    new "I came out here, deep in the forest, to this place. One of her favorite spots. Not far from where she died."

    old "I said my prayers and pulled out my dagger and slit my own throat."
    new "I said my prayers and pulled out my dagger and slit my own throat."

    old "He pointed to the side of a large stone, marked with a sickly dark red stain. Old, dried blood."
    new "He pointed to the side of a large stone, marked with a sickly dark red stain. Old, dried blood."

    old "As the blood spilled out, I could feel myself dying. I knew it. My mind went numb, and I slipped away and then just...black."
    new "As the blood spilled out, I could feel myself dying. I knew it. My mind went numb, and I slipped away and then just...black."

    old "But you didn't die..."
    new "But you didn't die..."

    old "A pained smile on his face."
    new "A pained smile on his face."

    old "No, I didn't die. Instead, I woke up here the next morning as if nothing had happened. All the wounds on my body, gone."
    new "No, I didn't die. Instead, I woke up here the next morning as if nothing had happened. All the wounds on my body, gone."

    old "I thought, perhaps I had dreamed it, but I saw the blood stain."
    new "I thought, perhaps I had dreamed it, but I saw the blood stain."

    old "Then I thought, perhaps a miracle. So I gathered my belongings and headed back to town."
    new "Then I thought, perhaps a miracle. So I gathered my belongings and headed back to town."

    old "When I arrived, the panic had broken out. The first attack of the Beast had taken place."
    new "When I arrived, the panic had broken out. The first attack of the Beast had taken place."

    old "There was such a commotion, I entirely forgot about trying to kill myself. Instead, I focussed on organizing the first hunt for the Beast."
    new "There was such a commotion, I entirely forgot about trying to kill myself. Instead, I focussed on organizing the first hunt for the Beast."

    old "When we found no trace, I returned to my bed that night and fell asleep."
    new "When we found no trace, I returned to my bed that night and fell asleep."

    old "He sighed deeply."
    new "He sighed deeply."

    old "That's when I had the dreams."
    new "That's when I had the dreams."

    old "I saw myself, rampaging through the forest."
    new "I saw myself, rampaging through the forest."

    old "My teeth were fangs, my hands claws, my skin thick and rough fur."
    new "My teeth were fangs, my hands claws, my skin thick and rough fur."

    old "And I tasted the blood."
    new "And I tasted the blood."

    old "The blood of that first girl I injured."
    new "The blood of that first girl I injured."

    old "Every night, the dreams of what I had done, returned. Reminding me. Haunting me."
    new "Every night, the dreams of what I had done, returned. Reminding me. Haunting me."

    old "How can a man become a beast?"
    new "How can a man become a beast?"

    old "Garret lowered his head."
    new "Garret lowered his head."

    old "For a while I thought the same. I imagined they were just nightmares."
    new "For a while I thought the same. I imagined they were just nightmares."

    old "Then it happened again, and I knew it was no nightmare. I knew facts of the next attack, that only the Beast could know."
    new "Then it happened again, and I knew it was no nightmare. I knew facts of the next attack, that only the Beast could know."

    old "I gathered my things and I returned to the forest. To this place. Where it all began."
    new "I gathered my things and I returned to the forest. To this place. Where it all began."

    old "And when night fell, I heard her."
    new "And when night fell, I heard her."

    old "Her?"
    new "Her?"

    old "My sister..."
    new "My sister..."

    old "Her voice. For a moment I thought she lived, so clearly could I hear it. Only then did I understand."
    new "Her voice. For a moment I thought she lived, so clearly could I hear it. Only then did I understand."

    old "It was her voice, but she had died in the forest and become a Woodland spirit."
    new "It was her voice, but she had died in the forest and become a Woodland spirit."

    old "Looking back, seeing where she died and how much she was connected to this place, it only makes sense."
    new "Looking back, seeing where she died and how much she was connected to this place, it only makes sense."

    old "What did she say?"
    new "What did she say?"

    old "She said that she had seen me in my torment. That she had saved me from myself. Saved my life."
    new "She said that she had seen me in my torment. That she had saved me from myself. Saved my life."

    old "Saved you?"
    new "Saved you?"

    old "Her desire to save me, and to be with me again, caused her to utter this curse on me."
    new "Her desire to save me, and to be with me again, caused her to utter this curse on me."

    old "A curse that would heal my wounds, save my life and make me a creature of the forest. A Beast."
    new "A curse that would heal my wounds, save my life and make me a creature of the forest. A Beast."

    old "Why would your own sister speak such a hex on you?"
    new "Why would your own sister speak such a hex on you?"

    old "These Woodland spirits...they see the world in troubled ways. Like looking through a fogged window."
    new "These Woodland spirits...they see the world in troubled ways. Like looking through a fogged window."

    old "That is why we leave the totems, to remind them of their old lives."
    new "That is why we leave the totems, to remind them of their old lives."

    old "But through a warped lense, their kind intentions can be...twisted."
    new "But through a warped lense, their kind intentions can be...twisted."

    old "So her true desire to save my life, and to see me returned to her, caused her wish to instead become a curse."
    new "So her true desire to save my life, and to see me returned to her, caused her wish to instead become a curse."

    old "And ever since, you have been the torment of your village's people..."
    new "And ever since, you have been the torment of your village's people..."

    old "Did you know?"
    new "Did you know?"

    old "Know?"
    new "Know?"

    old "That you are hurting them. Is it on purpose?"
    new "That you are hurting them. Is it on purpose?"

    old "Garret's face twisted in pain."
    new "Garret's face twisted in pain."

    old "Never..."
    new "Never..."

    old "But when the moon rises and my flesh twists and turns, I am no longer a man."
    new "But when the moon rises and my flesh twists and turns, I am no longer a man."

    old "My spirit is trapped in the flesh of a Beast, and I cannot do anything to stop it."
    new "My spirit is trapped in the flesh of a Beast, and I cannot do anything to stop it."

    old "I am powerless to see the horror that I inflict on these people...these people that rely on me for protection."
    new "I am powerless to see the horror that I inflict on these people...these people that rely on me for protection."

    old "New tears sprang from his eyes."
    new "New tears sprang from his eyes."

    old "Then it isn't your fault. You're not to blame."
    new "Then it isn't your fault. You're not to blame."

    old "I caused this! And even if I am no to blame, I am still the cause of it!"
    new "I caused this! And even if I am no to blame, I am still the cause of it!"

    old "So long as I live, I cannot be trusted."
    new "So long as I live, I cannot be trusted."

    old "Why now then? Why ask me to kill you?"
    new "Why now then? Why ask me to kill you?"

    old "Garret gestured towards the tree."
    new "Garret gestured towards the tree."

    old "A great metal chain ran around it, shattered and broken, some of the links were sprawled out across the grass."
    new "A great metal chain ran around it, shattered and broken, some of the links were sprawled out across the grass."

    old "I thought, if this is my fate, I will bind myself every night that I feel the transformation approach."
    new "I thought, if this is my fate, I will bind myself every night that I feel the transformation approach."

    old "And for many nights, it worked."
    new "And for many nights, it worked."

    old "I would change, but I would wake up having hurt nobody."
    new "I would change, but I would wake up having hurt nobody."

    old "For a while, I imagined that I could live with the curse like this. Live and hurt nobody."
    new "For a while, I imagined that I could live with the curse like this. Live and hurt nobody."

    old "But you did. You attacked again."
    new "But you did. You attacked again."

    old "Yes. The chain broke last night, and that poor Miller girl...Gods, if she dies, I don't know..."
    new "Yes. The chain broke last night, and that poor Miller girl...Gods, if she dies, I don't know..."

    old "Sarah crossed her arms and looked at Garret."
    new "Sarah crossed her arms and looked at Garret."

    old "The misery of his condition was written all over his face."
    new "The misery of his condition was written all over his face."

    old "Why me then? Why have me kill you?"
    new "Why me then? Why have me kill you?"

    old "I would have done it myself, but all this disaster has found its root in my suicide."
    new "I would have done it myself, but all this disaster has found its root in my suicide."

    old "If I tried to kill myself again, who knew what fresh curse my sister my speak out over me."
    new "If I tried to kill myself again, who knew what fresh curse my sister my speak out over me."

    old "No, I need you to do it."
    new "No, I need you to do it."

    old "You are a stranger in this town."
    new "You are a stranger in this town."

    old "You can kill me, return to town, and tell them that we found the Beast. Tell them that it killed me, and you killed it."
    new "You can kill me, return to town, and tell them that we found the Beast. Tell them that it killed me, and you killed it."

    old "The town will be save and they will remember me and my family as good people...not as the Monster I became."
    new "The town will be save and they will remember me and my family as good people...not as the Monster I became."

    old "You've made quite a plan for yourself."
    new "You've made quite a plan for yourself."

    old "And what about me? What if I don't want your blood on my hands?"
    new "And what about me? What if I don't want your blood on my hands?"

    old "Then think of all those you might save. The townsfolk."
    new "Then think of all those you might save. The townsfolk."

    old "And as for the blood on your hands, what is a few drops more? Surely you don't mean to tell me that you have not killed others before?"
    new "And as for the blood on your hands, what is a few drops more? Surely you don't mean to tell me that you have not killed others before?"

    old "Sarah felt an anger rise in her, but could not deny the charge."
    new "Sarah felt an anger rise in her, but could not deny the charge."

    old "So that is all that I am? A killer who can add one more soul to her sins?"
    new "So that is all that I am? A killer who can add one more soul to her sins?"

    old "She saw the pain in Garret's face."
    new "She saw the pain in Garret's face."

    old "Garret continued to plead with Sarah, grasping at her hands, begging."
    new "Garret continued to plead with Sarah, grasping at her hands, begging."

    old "Sarah...I would never have asked this of you. Of anyone. But there is no other way."
    new "Sarah...I would never have asked this of you. Of anyone. But there is no other way."

    old "We can go back to town! We can see if we might figure something, to help lift the curse, we can-"
    new "We can go back to town! We can see if we might figure something, to help lift the curse, we can-"

    old "Garret shouted out."
    new "Garret shouted out."

    old "The spirits are held at bay for now by the totems, but if they realize what is happening here, they can stop us!"
    new "The spirits are held at bay for now by the totems, but if they realize what is happening here, they can stop us!"

    old "Or worse, draw out the Beast from my soul and make me hurt you. Hurt...countless more."
    new "Or worse, draw out the Beast from my soul and make me hurt you. Hurt...countless more."

    old "He formed his hands to beg."
    new "He formed his hands to beg."

    old "No chain will hold me. This curse will not lift by any means that I know. If I don't end it here...how many more will fall victim to me?"
    new "No chain will hold me. This curse will not lift by any means that I know. If I don't end it here...how many more will fall victim to me?"

    old "Please...end this horror."
    new "Please...end this horror."

    old "Know that you will only do me a kindness."
    new "Know that you will only do me a kindness."

    old "Do as he asks, kill him"
    new "Do as he asks, kill him"

    old "Sarah looked down at Garret. Broken. Begging for death."
    new "Sarah looked down at Garret. Broken. Begging for death."

    old "And who was she to deny him it."
    new "And who was she to deny him it."

    old "His charge had been true. Her hands were stained with blood."
    new "His charge had been true. Her hands were stained with blood."

    old "She had killed more, for lesser reasons."
    new "She had killed more, for lesser reasons."

    old "What would be a few drops more?"
    new "What would be a few drops more?"

    old "Sarah drew her blade and leapt forward."
    new "Sarah drew her blade and leapt forward."

    old "In one swift and smooth motion, she brought the blade down on his neck."
    new "In one swift and smooth motion, she brought the blade down on his neck."

    old "The blow was fast and sudden. If he had any moment to respond, it was only an expression of gratitude."
    new "The blow was fast and sudden. If he had any moment to respond, it was only an expression of gratitude."

    old "Then he collapsed."
    new "Then he collapsed."

    old "Turning back to face him, Sarah saw his body sprawled out on the forest floor."
    new "Turning back to face him, Sarah saw his body sprawled out on the forest floor."

    old "Blood pooled out from the wound, but his body was motionless."
    new "Blood pooled out from the wound, but his body was motionless."

    old "She had killed the Beast."
    new "She had killed the Beast."

    old "But it had brought her little joy."
    new "But it had brought her little joy."

    old "Looking at it, she could not bring herself to think of all the possible lives she had saved or harm prevented."
    new "Looking at it, she could not bring herself to think of all the possible lives she had saved or harm prevented."

    old "She could only see the dead man who had deserved more than this."
    new "She could only see the dead man who had deserved more than this."

    old "Should she have tried harder?"
    new "Should she have tried harder?"

    old "He had asked her for this. It was a kindness. She had to remind herself of that."
    new "He had asked her for this. It was a kindness. She had to remind herself of that."

    old "There must be another way"
    new "There must be another way"

    old "If you have come looking for an executionor, I am not that person."
    new "If you have come looking for an executionor, I am not that person."

    old "I have tried nothing else, and yet you would ask me to kill you?"
    new "I have tried nothing else, and yet you would ask me to kill you?"

    old "Yes, I have killed others, I won't deny it."
    new "Yes, I have killed others, I won't deny it."

    old "But those were in battle. This...I have never murdered an innocent for so calous a reason."
    new "But those were in battle. This...I have never murdered an innocent for so calous a reason."

    old "Garret began to sob."
    new "Garret began to sob."

    old "I am not innocent!"
    new "I am not innocent!"

    old "I have wounded...I have killed..."
    new "I have wounded...I have killed..."

    old "Because of a hex put on you! That wasn't you, Garret! You do not deserve this fate, any more than you deserve death."
    new "Because of a hex put on you! That wasn't you, Garret! You do not deserve this fate, any more than you deserve death."

    old "Garret burried his head in hands."
    new "Garret burried his head in hands."

    old "There is no way...I will transform again. Hurt again..."
    new "There is no way...I will transform again. Hurt again..."

    old "Your spirits have laid out this curse, but I am not...I am not as most people."
    new "Your spirits have laid out this curse, but I am not...I am not as most people."

    old "She saw confusion dawn on his face."
    new "She saw confusion dawn on his face."

    old "I am saying that this world bends to me in ways unnatural."
    new "I am saying that this world bends to me in ways unnatural."

    old "And a curse imposed must surely also be able to be removed."
    new "And a curse imposed must surely also be able to be removed."

    old "I can...I can will it to be so."
    new "I can...I can will it to be so."

    old "Garret suddenly flinched."
    new "Garret suddenly flinched."

    old "The totems, they are-"
    new "The totems, they are-"

    old "One of the wooden totems exploded, splintering into countless fragments."
    new "One of the wooden totems exploded, splintering into countless fragments."

    old "Woodland Spirit\" \"Murderer!"
    new "Woodland Spirit\" \"Murderer!"

    old "The wind began to pick up."
    new "The wind began to pick up."

    old "Growing into a shrieking gyre, the trees in the forest began to bend and crack."
    new "Growing into a shrieking gyre, the trees in the forest began to bend and crack."

    old "Sarah covered her ears to protect herself from the thunderous noise."
    new "Sarah covered her ears to protect herself from the thunderous noise."

    old "Woodland Spirit\" \"You have brought one so wicked of soul to these sacred forests!"
    new "Woodland Spirit\" \"You have brought one so wicked of soul to these sacred forests!"

    old "No! Please! Don't harm her! She had nothing to do with this. This was my doing, please!"
    new "No! Please! Don't harm her! She had nothing to do with this. This was my doing, please!"

    old "Garret frantically pleaded with the spirit."
    new "Garret frantically pleaded with the spirit."

    old "Woodland Spirit\" \"She tries to take you away from me. Turn you against me!"
    new "Woodland Spirit\" \"She tries to take you away from me. Turn you against me!"

    old "Please! Don't hurt her, she didn't-"
    new "Please! Don't hurt her, she didn't-"

    old "Garret suddenly hunched over."
    new "Garret suddenly hunched over."

    old "A deep groan of pain roared out from his throat as he collapsed to the ground."
    new "A deep groan of pain roared out from his throat as he collapsed to the ground."

    old "His hands dug into the ground, ripping up grass and dirt."
    new "His hands dug into the ground, ripping up grass and dirt."

    old "Sarah tried to move towards him, but the storm had grown so violent that she could barely advance."
    new "Sarah tried to move towards him, but the storm had grown so violent that she could barely advance."

    old "Sarah! Run...I can't..."
    new "Sarah! Run...I can't..."

    old "Sarah watched as his spine snapped."
    new "Sarah watched as his spine snapped."

    old "Then the bones in his arms and legs."
    new "Then the bones in his arms and legs."

    old "Garret screamed out in more pain."
    new "Garret screamed out in more pain."

    old "Woodland Spirit\" \"You seek to rob him of his true nature!"
    new "Woodland Spirit\" \"You seek to rob him of his true nature!"

    old "Woodland Spirit\" \"I shall set you free, Brother!"
    new "Woodland Spirit\" \"I shall set you free, Brother!"

    old "Sarah watched as Garret's jaw went so wide, it almost seemed as if it had split apart."
    new "Sarah watched as Garret's jaw went so wide, it almost seemed as if it had split apart."

    old "In his mouth, his teeth had sharpened like razors. Rows of fangs, protruding out."
    new "In his mouth, his teeth had sharpened like razors. Rows of fangs, protruding out."

    old "The violence on his body should have surely been the end of him, but Sarah saw he still lived."
    new "The violence on his body should have surely been the end of him, but Sarah saw he still lived."

    old "Still lived and sufferd."
    new "Still lived and sufferd."

    old "Screamed as his body violently underwent the horrors of this curse."
    new "Screamed as his body violently underwent the horrors of this curse."

    old "Suffered the transformation, from man to beast."
